===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|apotecaire|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|ML.|en}} {{term|apothecarius||storekeeper|lang=la}}, from {{term|lang=la|apotheca||shop, store}}, earlier {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|lang=la|apotheca||repository, storehouse, warehouse}}, from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|lang=grc|ἀποθήκη||tr=apothēkē|a repository, storehouse}}, from {{term|ἀποτίθημι|lang=grc|tr=apotithēmi||to put away}}, from {{term|lang=grc|ἀπό|tr=apo||away}} (English {{term|apo-|lang=en}}, PIE cognate to {{term|of|lang=en}}) + {{term|lang=grc|τίθημι|tr=tithēmi||to put}} (PIE cognate of English {{term|do|lang=en}}).

